{{Infobox building | name = Solstice on the Park | alternate_names = | building_type = Residential | architectural_style = | classification = | location = | address = | location_city = [[Chicago]] | location_country = [[United States]] | est_completion = | topped_out_date = | completion_date = 2018 | closing_date = | cost = | height = | architectural = | tip = | antenna_spire = | material = | size = | floor_area = | architect = [[Jeanne Gang]] }} '''Solstice on the Park''' is a residential building in [[Chicago]] designed by architect [[Jeanne Gang]] and completed in 2018.
==Development== The building was originally designed in 2006 as condominium building, but economic conditions stalled construction.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chicago.curbed.com/2015/2/13/9992270/is-the-sun-rising-again-for-solstice-on-the-park|title=The Sun Is Rising Again on Studio Gang's Solstice on the Park|date=13 February 2015|publisher=Curbed|accessdate=12 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/columnists/kamin/ct-biz-gang-tower-kamin-0722-story.html|title=Made with the shade: A striking Jeanne Gang tower elevates its lakefront setting in Hyde Park|last=Kamin|first=Blair|date=24 July 2018|publisher=Chicago Tribune|accessdate=12 September 2018}}</ref> Revised plans for the building were approved in early 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dnainfo.com/chicago/20160219/hyde-park/jeanne-gang-designed-apartments-for-hyde-park-get-ok-from-city/|title=Jeanne Gang-Designed Apartments for Hyde Park Get OK from the City|last=Cholke|first=Sam|date=19 February 2016|publisher=dnainfo|accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref> Later that year, the developer announced construction would begin before 2017, and that tenants could begin living in the building as early as 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dnainfo.com/chicago/20160913/hyde-park/jeanne-gang-explains-why-she-changed-solstice-on-park-design/|title=Jeanne Gang Explains Why She Changed The Solstice On The Park Design|last=Cholke|first=Sam|date=13 September 2016|publisher=dnainfo|accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref> Work began in October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chicago.curbed.com/2016/10/20/13344608/chicago-construction-hyde-park-solstice-tower-studio-gang|title=Work underway on Hyde Park’s long-planned Solstice tower|last=Koziarz|first=Jay|date=20 October 2016|publisher=Curbed|accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref> The building is designed to provide maximum natural light.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chicago.curbed.com/2018/9/17/17822868/solstice-on-the-park-hyde-park-studio-gang|title=Inside Jeanne Gang’s Solstice on the Park|last=Koziarz|first=Jay|date=17 September 2018|publisher=Curbed|accessdate=17 September 2018}}</ref>
Financing was provided by Arkansas-based lender [[Bank of the Ozarks]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagobusiness.com/article/20170621/CRED03/170629954/bank-of-the-ozarks-finances-solstice-on-the-park-in-hyde-park|title=Bank of the Ozarks strikes in Hyde Park|last=Gallun|first=Alby|date=21 June 2017|publisher=Crain's Chicago Business|accessdate=12 September 2018}}</ref>
